title: For Trade:  GAMO Whisper air rifle 1200fps
postcontent: This is the original GAMO Whisper with noise reducer.  It fires .177 pellets.  It will fire 1250fps with lead pellets, or 1000 with the slightly lighter coated pellets .I've taken out large rodents with this (original reason for buying, had a neighbor who was a pet hoarder) and done some target shooting.  It also works great to scare off eagles trying to snatch your chickens, as it won't penetrate their feathers, instead startling them.  It WILL take out pigeons .  It's a great gun, fun to shoot, whether you are using the scope or the fiber optic sights .While it may not sound whisper silent to you when firing, the baffle actually directs the sound back and to the sides, so it won't startle whatever you're shooting at.  Which means if you're shooting rats in your neighbor's yard, it won't alert them or their dogs.Action (piston assembly) is blued steel and looks like a regular gun barrel quality .  Barrel forward of the break is a lined polymer composite, and the stock is weatherproof polymer .Comes with four time of pellets in various styles- the Master Point and Hunter are the same, conical pellets with a dense pointed end.  The Magnum is similar, but with a domed end that I found is more effective for pests (maybe it increases the impact shock). The Match has a flat face, for punching clean holes in paper targets.I built a gun rack for it that can either be wall mounted with a french cleat or just sit on a shelf. Has built in shelf with three recessed pockets to hold ammo tins.  Made of pine, and unfinished so you can stain or clear coat it, and put some felt or rubber in the gun hooks .Willing to sell, but I'm more interested in trades.

title: For Sale:  SIG MOSQUITO 22LR + 2x10RD MAG OFF ROSTER HANDGUN
postcontent: For sale is Sig Mosquito 22LR with 2x 10rd magazineCondition: GOOD, some minor wear but no heavy scratch or deep cut.The gun was purchased brand new in late 2015 and has had less than 300 rounds through it.The mosquito is no longer on CA roster so you can only buy it used from a CA owner.HONEST WORDS: if you are looking for a handgun with reliable functionality, the sig mosquito is not the one. This gun is infamous for having lots of issues (almost all kinds of issues that can happen to a handgun happens with the mosquito) which led to numerous videos and articles showing how to fix them. I have fixed the fail-to-feed by polishing the feeding ramp. I also fixed the fail-to-eject by polishing the extractor pin as well as the rear cyclinder. These fixes greatly reduced the rate of fail-to-feed and fail-to-eject, however, they still occur once every 10 rounds or so. Besides, there is also the fail-to-fire which happens 1-2 every 10 rounds which I did not have time to look into. I have tried this gun with several different types of 22LR ammo (CCI, Federal, Amscor,...). So far, the one that produced the least problem was Federal bulk ammo (the target grade 325rd brick). The last time I worked on this gun was more than a year ago. So this gun has been sitting in the case since. If you are interested, send me an offer.Cash only.
